        "comment": {
            "name": "comment",
            "type": "com.atlassian.jira.issue.fields.CommentSystemField",
            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/29253",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=mikaelkael",
                        "name": "mikaelkael",
                        "displayName": "Mickael Perraud",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "In this case, Zend_Db_Adapter_Abstract will throw an exception with _checkRequiredOptions():\n{code}\nZend_Db_Adapter_Exception(\"Configuration array must have a key for 'dbname' that names the database instance\")\n{code}\n\nSince SVN5014, this part of code is unused.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=mikaelkael",
                        "name": "mikaelkael",
                        "displayName": "Mickael Perraud",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-03-03T13:40:40.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-03-03T13:43:59.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/29260",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=stevejordan",
                        "name": "stevejordan",
                        "displayName": "Steve Jordan",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "sorry, I wasn't very clear in the description.\n\ninside the _connect() function there is the following code:\n{code:title=Zend_Db_Adapter_Oracle::_connect() - partial}\n        if (isset($this->_config['dbname'])) {\n            $this->_connection = @oci_connect(\n                $this->_config['username'],\n                $this->_config['password'],\n                $this->_config['dbname']);\n        } else {\n            $this->_connection = oci_connect(\n                $this->_config['username'],\n                $this->_config['password']);\n        }\n{code}\n\nat the moment a check is made to see if dbname has been declared somewhere, and if it has oci_connect has it's errors suppressed (@).\nThere is no error suppression when dbname has not been set.\n\nThis is an inconsistency, and caused me some issues while trying to diagnose a connection issue (The exception thrown contained no useful information)\n\nI hope this is clearer.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=stevejordan",
                        "name": "stevejordan",
                        "displayName": "Steve Jordan",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-03-04T06:18:27.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-03-04T06:18:27.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/29275",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=mikaelkael",
                        "name": "mikaelkael",
                        "displayName": "Mickael Perraud",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "You were clear, no problem ;).\n\nBased on actual trunk, I think this code is unreachable. So we could replace:\n{code}\nif (isset($this->_config['dbname'])) {\n    $this->_connection = @oci_connect(\n        $this->_config['username'],\n        $this->_config['password'],\n        $this->_config['dbname']);\n} else {\n    $this->_connection = oci_connect(\n        $this->_config['username'],\n        $this->_config['password']);\n}\n{code}\nby:\n{code}\n$this->_connection = @oci_connect(\n    $this->_config['username'],\n    $this->_config['password'],\n    $this->_config['dbname']);\n{code}\n\nBecause $this->_config['dbname'] is mandatory, if it misses, then you have an exception thrown by Zend_Db_Adapter_Abstract::_checkRequiredOptions() before entering in Zend_Db_Adapter_Oracle::_connect()",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=mikaelkael",
                        "name": "mikaelkael",
                        "displayName": "Mickael Perraud",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-03-04T11:14:28.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-03-04T11:14:28.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/29292",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=stevejordan",
                        "name": "stevejordan",
                        "displayName": "Steve Jordan",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I see what your saying.\nIt sounds like a good idea to remove code which will never be run.\n\nBut the problem which I was having (with the empty Exception messages) will still occur in your replacement code, because you still have the @ suppressing error messages.\n\nIf you look at the next code block in the file:\n{code:title = Zend_Db_Adapter_Oracle::_connect() - partial}\n\/\/ check the connection\nif (!$this->_connection) {\n            \/**\n             * @see Zend_Db_Adapter_Oracle_Exception\n             *\/\n            require_once 'Zend\/Db\/Adapter\/Oracle\/Exception.php';\n            throw new Zend_Db_Adapter_Oracle_Exception(oci_error());\n        }\n\n{code}",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=stevejordan",
                        "name": "stevejordan",
                        "displayName": "Steve Jordan",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-03-05T08:44:18.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-03-05T08:44:18.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/29293",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=stevejordan",
                        "name": "stevejordan",
                        "displayName": "Steve Jordan",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "sorry, I hit \"Add\" too soon.\n\nthe call to oci_error() will never return anything while the oci_connect() errors are suppressed.\n\nSo my suggestion is to remove the @ before oci_connect.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=stevejordan",
                        "name": "stevejordan",
                        "displayName": "Steve Jordan",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-03-05T08:45:57.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-03-05T08:45:57.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/29318",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=mikaelkael",
                        "name": "mikaelkael",
                        "displayName": "Mickael Perraud",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "{quote}\nthe call to oci_error() will never return anything while the oci_connect() errors are suppressed.\n{quote}\n\nFor me, it's false, see these examples:\n{code}\n<?php\noci_connect('user', 'good_password', 'database');\nprint_r(oci_error());\n{code}\n=> return nothing\n----\n{code}\n<?php\noci_connect('user', 'bad_password', 'database');\nprint_r(oci_error());\n{code}\n=>\n{code}\n<br \/>\n<b>Warning<\/b>:  oci_connect() [<a href='function.oci-connect'>function.oci-connect<\/a>]: ORA-01017: invalid username\/password; logon denied in <b>D:\\web\\www\\test_oracle.php<\/b> on line <b>2<\/b><br \/>\nArray\n(\n    [code] => 1017\n    [message] => ORA-01017: invalid username\/password; logon denied\n    [offset] => 0\n    [sqltext] => \n)\n{code}\n----\n{code}\n<?php\n@oci_connect('user', 'bad_password', 'database');\nprint_r(oci_error());\n{code}\n=>\n{code}\nArray\n(\n    [code] => 1017\n    [message] => ORA-01017: invalid username\/password; logon denied\n    [offset] => 0\n    [sqltext] => \n)\n{code}\n----\nThe goal of @ is simply to suppress the warning but oci_error() is always populated.\n\nNo?",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=mikaelkael",
                        "name": "mikaelkael",
                        "displayName": "Mickael Perraud",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-03-06T12:58:13.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-03-06T12:58:13.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/29359",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=stevejordan",
                        "name": "stevejordan",
                        "displayName": "Steve Jordan",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "It looks like I have misunderstood the purpose of @\n\nIn which case the exception thrown needs to contain at least the code and message, something like:\n\n{code}\n\/\/ check the connection\nif (!$this->_connection) {\n            \/**\n             * @see Zend_Db_Adapter_Oracle_Exception\n             *\/\n            require_once 'Zend\/Db\/Adapter\/Oracle\/Exception.php';\n            $errorMessageArray = oci_error();\n            throw new Zend_Db_Adapter_Oracle_Exception($errorMessageArray[code] . ': ' . $errorMessageArray[message]);\n        }\n{code}\n\n?",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=stevejordan",
                        "name": "stevejordan",
                        "displayName": "Steve Jordan",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-03-10T04:19:02.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-03-10T04:19:02.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/29391",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=mikaelkael",
                        "name": "mikaelkael",
                        "displayName": "Mickael Perraud",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Open Zend\/Db\/Adapter\/Oracle\/Exception.php, you will see how this is managed",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=mikaelkael",
                        "name": "mikaelkael",
                        "displayName": "Mickael Perraud",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-03-11T01:57:25.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-03-11T01:57:25.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/29392",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=stevejordan",
                        "name": "stevejordan",
                        "displayName": "Steve Jordan",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I see. That makes sense now.\n\nSo in my case the lack of an error message is down to oci_error not returning one, rather than the framework's processing.\n\nThanks for pointing me in the right direction.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=stevejordan",
                        "name": "stevejordan",
                        "displayName": "Steve Jordan",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-03-11T02:29:59.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-03-11T02:29:59.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/29488",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=mikaelkael",
                        "name": "mikaelkael",
                        "displayName": "Mickael Perraud",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "The unreachable code was removed with SVN 14324 to close this issue.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=mikaelkael",
                        "name": "mikaelkael",
                        "displayName": "Mickael Perraud",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-03-15T07:21:45.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-03-15T07:21:45.000+0000"
                }
            ]
        }
